                    <p class=3D"text">Linear programming is the process of =
taking various linear inequalities (called "constraints") relating to some =
situation, and finding the best value obtainable under those conditions. A =
typical example would be taking the limitations of materials and labor, and=
 then determining the optimal production levels for maximal profits under t=
hose conditions.</p>
